reviewText:
I seek out the Paley Fest interviews for all my favorite shows and this one did not disappoint. I love Jessica Lange and all the rest of the actors on the show. It is so much fun to hear them talk about the show and see them interact together!

Give this a try, I promise if you like this show you won't be disappointed! Hey, I watched this Paley Fest before I watched a single episode of AHS Asylum and I enjoyed this so much that that is why I watched the show!
I watched all of season two in one day and I can say it kept me on my toes. I like the idea how the show is different each season...
As a huge fan of the show, I loved this panel.  It was so interesting and insightful to hear from the cast and crew.  It made me want to watch American Horrorr Story all over again, again.
I love American Horror Story and I really like watching the Paleyfest after the season.  I am thinking about buying the whole season for the extra's on the DVD.

All the way through the entire episode you become lost in the movie and its hard to not watch the every episode one after another with out a break, it is that good! The best I have seen in years. I am looking forward to more like this one.
This show is the Best!! The storyline and acting is amazing!!  I love every season and this show was terrific.
Interesting and sometimes fun.
Loved watching this typing of cast and crew! Very entertaining and informative!
Very entertaining, fun quirky people to listen to.........
Wonderful to see and hear. Wish I could watch the ones they did every year.
Loved this. Perfect for the die hard fans.
this is my favorite show and seeing them live answer questions i just loved it
Love it!
Awesome series!!! Bizarre and different makes this a uniquely interesting combination.

I love these Paley shows to get the scoop on all the "behind the scenes" stuff from my favorite shows!  I've never been a _horror genre_ fan, but the acting and writing have really captured my attention.  What a great cast!

Highly recommended!
When I find myself bored,I always watch AHS shows or interviews! I love AHS!

I love Jessica Lange as herself, even more than her characters.  Its remarkable to see how different she is from her characters.  I didn't appreciate the range of her acting skills as much before I saw her personality shine through.  I loved this!
love them

Very cool to see the real side of some of my favorite actors. Especially Jessica Lange, she is such an interesting and talented woman. She's all grace. Not to mention that American Horror Story is my favorite show ever. Ryan Murphy is so delightfully twisted! It's great to hear where some of my favorite scenes/episodes came to fruition.

If you don't like spine chilling edge of your seat thrillers DON'T watch this! On the other hand,
if you DO like great writing, great acting, great stage sets and an all frills twist and turn production, this is the
show you are looking for.  My stomach was in a knot throughout.  I did a marathon and gave myself no breaks. I actually forgot to eat !
Jessica Lang is just extraordinary.  This woman wears more hats in one production than some actors do in a whole career.  All of the actors are terrific. I had to keep reminding myself that this was acting.
The first season was good. The second season was better.
I highly recommend this show.  Each season is a completely different story with many of the same actors so you could watch season 2 without watching season 1 and you will have missed nothing.
The only issue I ever have with these types of shows are the ideas they might be giving to the crazies out there.
This series is so addicting. Can't stop watching it!!!!
Great panel discussion about the show!
Great show
Love love love this show
The actors take on  their characters was interesting and the fact that they didn't seem to know where the show was going over the course of the season was also interesting.
Interesting, but could have been better.  I would have liked more clips of the series and discussion about that with the actors.
AMAZING!!! SUCH RAULSON. MUCH WOW.
Entertaining to watch characters in their own  persona. The host could have better questions to each of the celebrities rather than just Jessica talking.
great show
Love it
The best.  So much fun to watch the cast and crew as themselves.  Love it.
Love these people!
A well made story with some of the best actors on the planet. Excellent show.
I am in the middle of the third season. Love the concept and all the actors. Did not really like the ending of the first season that much. It was just.. meh. Have enjoyed all the other episodes.
nan

I love hearing the actors point of view, I like Jessica Lange's comment about her singing in the "name game episode." That was actually one of my favorite episodes.  I also loved looking at Pepper without makeup and all the other actors, I would love to buy this as a DVD for my collection.
